      "https://w3id.org/ftr#identifier": {
        "@type": "xsd:anyURI",
        "@value": "https://w3id.org/fair-metrics/general/FM_R1-1_M_DbStdLic"
      },
      "dc:title": "FAIR Metric - R1.1 - Metadata - Database-level licenses",
      "http://vivoweb.org/ontology/core#abbreviation": "FM_R1-1_M_DbStdLic",
      "dcat:landingPage": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/fair-metrics/general/FM_R1-1_M_DbStdLic"
      },
      "dc:description": "<p>This metric evaluates whether there is at least one \n    licence declared at the database level in the FAIRsharing registry \n    record associated with the identifier under evaluation \n    (see FAIRsharing\n     [documentation for licences](https://fairsharing.gitbook.io/fairsharing/record-sections-and-fields/licences-and-support-links/licences)</p>\n\n<p>R1.1 requires that metadata be released with a clear and accessible data usage licence. \nThe purpose of this principle is to ensure that reuse conditions are explicitly stated and \nlegally unambiguous. This metric evaluates whether there is at least one licence declared \nat the database level in the FAIRsharing registry record associated with the identifier under \nevaluation. Under this interpretation, the evaluation retrieves the FAIRsharing registry record \nfor the owning database and checks for the presence of one or more values in the “Licences” \nfield, as defined in the \n[documentation for licences](https://fairsharing.gitbook.io/fairsharing/record-sections-and-fields/licences-and-support-links/licences)\nThese licences represent usage conditions known to apply within the database. \nA resource satisfies this metric if the FAIRsharing registry record for the database \nlists at least one recognised licence. While a useful measure, this information only \nprovides a list of licences that apply to content, and does not explicitly state which \none applies to which research objects, nor does it ensure that the database uses a licence \nfor every research object. However, in cases where the licence information is not provided \nwithin the resolved metadata, this will provide some extra information.  Communities may wish \nto use this metric in conjunction with others that will evaluate resolved metadata where the \nspecific licence format and structure is known. Note that, in order for this metric to function, \n    tests must know the FAIRsharing database record URL/DOI so that FAIRsharing metadata may be \n    retrieved. This can be done in a variety of ways, e.g. using the FAIRsharing API to find \n    possible matches between the identifier and registered databases, hard \ncoding the FAIRsharing record identifier, or expecting it to be provided as a second argument to the test.</p>\n",
      "dcat:keyword": [
